# Explicit build targets for JS transpilation (SWC).
#
# These widen the compilation target so Next.js/SWC lowers modern syntax
# (optional chaining ?., nullish coalescing ??, logical assignment ??=/||=/&&=,
# private class fields) down to syntax that older Safari / iOS Safari can parse.
# Combined with `transpilePackages` in next.config.ts, this makes the app code
# AND the bundled dependencies (motion, lenis, etc.) safe to load on older
# WebKit, which is the root cause of the page failing to load on some devices.
#
# Note on CSS: Tailwind v4's Lightning CSS does read these targets, but the
# only resulting change is that it emits `vertical-align: initial` instead of
# `vertical-align: baseline` in a few reset/utility rules. `baseline` IS the
# initial value of `vertical-align`, so the two are identical and the rendered
# design is unchanged. No utilities, colors, spacing, or layout are affected.
chrome >= 64
edge >= 79
firefox >= 67
opera >= 51
safari >= 12
ios_saf >= 12
samsung >= 9
and_chr >= 64
